**![](data:image/png;base64,)**The action icons displayed at the top of the CSV Reader's configuration page allow to perform global actions on the CSV data structure.

**Icon**

**Action**

**Description**

![](data:image/png;base64,)

[**Import structure**](/doxee-platform/docs/2-dt3-csv-reader-global-actions#importing-a-data-structure)

Define the structure to read CSV input files using an existing CSV file.

![](data:image/png;base64,)

**Download structure**

Download a copy of the data structure to your local filesystem in CSV format (for example: *DTE_9490744117271127239_Reader1.csv*).

![](data:image/png;base64,)

[**Settings**](/doxee-platform/docs/2-dt3-csv-reader-global-actions#configuring-the-csv-readers-general-settings)

Define the general settings of the CSV Reader resource.

### Importing a data structure
This feature allows to define the structure to read CSV input files using an existing CSV file.

The functionality is useful, for example, if you want to import the structure of an existing CSV file instead of manually defining the required fields.

> Note

It is always possible to modify the imported structure.

> Warning

This action will permanently delete and overwrite the existing data structure.

- Open the CSV Reader resource in the configuration editor as described in [Configuring DT3 Project Resources](/doxee-platform/docs/configuring-dt3-project-resources).

- Click  ![](data:image/png;base64,) (**Import structure**). The following dialog appears:

![](data:image/jpeg;base64,)

- Configure the required parameters:

**Field**

**Description**

**Separator**

Select the character separator used in the CSV file. The possible options are:

**Colon (:) **

- **Pound (#) **

- **Tab**

- **Pipe (|) **

- **Comma (,) **

- **Semicolon (;)**

**Encoding**

Select the encoding of the CSV file.

**Set fields names from file content**

Select the **First line contains fields names **option to indicate that the CSV file's header row contains the names of the data fields.

- Drag &amp; drop the CSV file to import into the highlighted area, or click **browse **to select if from your local filesystem.

![](data:image/jpeg;base64,)

> Tip

Click ![](data:image/png;base64,)  to remove the selected file.

- Click **CONTINUE**.

> Important

If a data structure has already been defined for the CSV Reader, the system notifies you that importing a new structure file will discard the existing data. Click **YES, CONTINUE **to proceed anyway.

![](data:image/jpeg;base64,)

The new data structure is automatically loaded into the CSV Reader's configuration, overwriting any existing data; for example:

![](data:image/jpeg;base64,)

### Configuring the CSV Reader's general settings
- Open the XML Reader resource in the configuration editor as described in [Configuring DT3 Project Resources](/doxee-platform/docs/configuring-dt3-project-resources).

- Click  ![](data:image/png;base64,) (**Settings**). The **Settings **panel is displayed on the right; for example:

![](data:image/jpeg;base64,)

- Configure the required parameters:

**Section**

**Parameter**

**Description**

**General**

**Name**

Name of the CSV Reader

**Description**

*(optional) *Brief description of the CSV Reader

**Reader options**

**File type**

Data structure type (default value: "CSV")

> Note

This field is not editable.

**Character separator**

Select the character separator used in the CSV file. The possible options are:

**Colon (:) **

- **Pound (#) **

- **Tab**

- **Pipe (|) **

- **Comma (,) **

- **Semicolon (;)**

**Encoding**

File encoding (default value: "UTF-8") 

> Note

This field is not editable.

**Input method**

Input method (default value: "Import data from source") 

> Note

This field is not editable.

**Structure**

**Schema name**

View and edit the name of the current data schema.

> Tip

The **Applied to **section lists the Data Transformation components using this data schema, allowing you to evaluate the impacts of adding, deleting or modifying its elements.
